- Always finalize with `npm run build`, `npm run lint --fix` and `npm run format` before commit. Fix errors; ignore warnings.
- Log a one-line markdown summary in `.cursor-updates` after every interaction.
- Commit using `git add .; git commit -m "..."; git push` with structured present-tense commit messages (e.g., `feat: add auth module`).
- Maintain clean, well-structured code following ESLint and Prettier standards.
- Functions have clear TypeScript types.
- Use explicit types; avoid `any`.
- Enable strict mode in `tsconfig.json`.
- Update `.env.example` for new environment variables.
- DO NOT use mock data